•	Have   five (5) years of working experience in the Information Technology (IT)   field, especially in the area of infrastructure planning, data centre   operations and network management;
    •	Have at least three (3) years hands-on practical experience in operating   enterprise routers/switches, firewalls, load balancers, Internet proxy   servers, bandwidth management systems, IDS/IPS, and server/platform   systems;
    •	Have at least two (2) years of experience in leading a team in a similar   capacity;
    •	Designing and implementing new network solutions and/or improving the   efficiency of current networks
    •	Installing, configuring and supporting network equipment including   routers, proxy servers, switches, WAN accelerators, DNS and DHCP
    •	Configuring firewalls, routing and switching to maximise network   efficiency and security
    •	Maximising network performance through ongoing monitoring and   troubleshooting
    •	Arranging scheduled upgrades
    •	Investigating faults in the network
    •	Updating network equipment to the latest firmware releases
    •	Automation skillsets such as Python, Ansible, Chef is preferred

Certification - CCNP and above